description: The Juvenile Services Education System (JSES) provides students residing in the Department of Juvenile Services (DJS) residential facilities located across Maryland with daily instructional programming and services.  Students enrolled in JSES are provided instruction in all core content areas as well as access to designated career technology educational course comparable to those offered in the other 24 local school systems within Maryland.   JSES functions as the local school system for these students and provides services to ensure optimal educational access.   Opportunities are tailored for each student in order to promote his or her effective and positive transition to home, community and school from DJS facilities.

bid_attachment_description: MRDCC and BCBIC Elevator Service  IFB
organization_name: Maryland Department of Public Safety and Correctional Svcs
short_description: Elevator Preventative Maintenance at BCBIC and MRDCC, Baltimore, MD Contract No. KU-001-180-M02
description: SUMMARY OR WORK: This is a three (3) year contract to provide elevator repair and preventative maintenance services for two (2) elevators in the Baltimore Region. The first (1st) is at Maryland Reception Diagnostic Correctional Center (MRDCC) located at 550 East Madison Street, Baltimore, MD 21202 and the second (2nd) is at Baltimore City Booking and Intake Center (BCBIC) located at 300 East Madison Street, Baltimore, MD 21202. Service to be done in strict accordance with the Contract Documents subject to the terms and conditions of the contract. The Bidders shall print on their own stationary a quote which includes costs for all project requirements and submit to the Owner (DPSCS, Division of Capital Construction and Facilities Maintenance, Attention: Procurement Officer) in a sealed envelope which clearly indicates that the envelope contains a sealed bid for this project, the bid due date, and the name and address of the Bidder. No bid will be accepted after the due date and time. DPSCS/DCCFM ELECTRONIC DOCUMENTS AND FORMS OF THE 'INVITATION FOR BID' PACKAGE ARE THE ONLY OFFICIAL DOCUMENTS AND THEREFORE, ONLY THESE MAY BE USED FOR BIDDING PURPOSES. CONTRACT AWARD SHALL BE BASED ON OFFICIAL DOCUMENTS ISSUED BY THE ISSUING OFFICE.

short_description: Elevator Preventative Maintenance at BCBIC and MRDCC, Baltimore, MD Contract No. KU-001-180-M02
description: SUMMARY OR WORK: This is a three (3) year contract to provide elevator repair and preventative maintenance services for two (2) elevators in the Baltimore Region. The first (1st) is at Maryland Reception Diagnostic Correctional Center (MRDCC) located at 550 East Madison Street, Baltimore, MD 21202 and the second (2nd) is at Baltimore City Booking and Intake Center (BCBIC) located at 300 East Madison Street, Baltimore, MD 21202. Service to be done in strict accordance with the Contract Documents subject to the terms and conditions of the contract. The Bidders shall print on their own stationary a quote which includes costs for all project requirements and submit to the Owner (DPSCS, Division of Capital Construction and Facilities Maintenance, Attention: Procurement Officer) in a sealed envelope which clearly indicates that the envelope contains a sealed bid for this project, the bid due date, and the name and address of the Bidder. No bid will be accepted after the due date and time. DPSCS/DCCFM ELECTRONIC DOCUMENTS AND FORMS OF THE 'INVITATION FOR BID' PACKAGE ARE THE ONLY OFFICIAL DOCUMENTS AND THEREFORE, ONLY THESE MAY BE USED FOR BIDDING PURPOSES. CONTRACT AWARD SHALL BE BASED ON OFFICIAL DOCUMENTS ISSUED BY THE ISSUING OFFICE.

description: The Juvenile Services Education System (JSES) provides students residing in the Department of Juvenile Services (DJS) residential facilities located across Maryland with daily instructional programming and services.  Students enrolled in JSES are provided instruction in all core content areas as well as access to designated career technology educational course comparable to those offered in the other 24 local school systems within Maryland.   JSES functions as the local school system for these students and provides services to ensure optimal educational access.   Opportunities are tailored for each student in order to promote his or her effective and positive transition to home, community and school from DJS facilities.
